pr_review_comment_body:
A minor note: whenever you have `TYPE var = static_cast<TYPE>(...)` it's better to declare the variable as `auto`. That way you repeat yourself less, and the line is shorter too:
```C++
auto d_c = static_cast<const double*>(dt_exemplars->columns[i]->data());
// vs
const double* d_c = static_cast<const double*>(dt_exemplars->columns[i]->data());
``` 

Also, in this particular case you could have declared `d_c` first, and then
```C++
const double* d_c = c->elements_r();
```

Yeah, I had that initially. But then, having to pass 6 or 7 arguments to that function turned me off and made me roll it back. Another idea to get rid of the `else` and the indentation would be to do.

```python
if hasattr(args, 'func'):
    return args.func(args, chain_config)
```

If you add this to `externs.rs` just below `store_utf8`:

```
///
/// Store a buffer of utf8 bytes to pass to Python. This will end up as a Python `unicode`.
///
#[cfg(unix)]
pub fn store_utf8_osstr(utf8: &OsStr) -> Value {
  use std::os::unix::ffi::OsStrExt;
  let bytes = utf8.as_bytes();
  with_externs(|e| (e.store_utf8)(e.context, bytes.as_ptr(), bytes.len() as u64).into())
}
```

and here instead call `externs::store_utf8(item.as_os_str());`

you should be able to close https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/issues/6302 :)

